The article discusses the current state of the American economy and the perception of it among Americans. It mentions a media campaign that is trying to convince people that the economy is worse than it actually is. However, the National Federation of Independent Business has reported that its small business optimism index reached its second highest level in history in July. The survey also showed high numbers of owners reporting current job openings or plans to create jobs. Overall, the article suggests that Americans are recognizing and acknowledging the strength of the economy.